# UUM-8D GaiaFTCL — context protection (limb stability)

Keep the **IDE limb** within bounded entropy so it does not destabilize the manifold session.

## Limits

- Prefer **summaries** over unbounded paste chains when context grows large.
- **Anti-loop:** no unbounded retries (cap sensible attempts); no recursive subagent trees without explicit termination.
- **Subagents / tasks:** must declare success/failure criteria and bounds before spawn.

## If stuck

Same failure repeatedly → **stop**, report **BLOCKED** with witness; do not spin.

## UUM-8D reading

Unbounded context is **uncontrolled torsion** in the assistance layer; **settle** or **refuse**.
